          <p><span class="assign-text-lead">SUMMARY</span>
          Last week we looked at your passions and strengths and how to learn more about jobs that might be a good fit through informational interviews. Most of those informational interviews will likely come from someone in your network. This week, you’re going to get practice pushing beyond your comfort zone and learn why it’s so important to be connected with people outside your circle of family and friends. So, get ready! You’re going to explore the power of investing in the relationships in your network, and take inventory of the connections you have with others. In you coaching cohort, you are going to discover the difference between strong ties and weak ties and the benefits of the unique relationships you have with people who are close to you (like your family, friends) and connections that are not as close, but still are important to your support and development. You will gain more confidence in cultivating relationships with more weak ties, resulting in a richer network of resources and opportunities. 
          </p>
          <p>
          You will also build on the power of relationships and using your networks to achieve things. Leadership begins with understanding yourself: your values, your motivation, your story.  But leadership is also about enabling others to achieve purpose.  
          </p> 
        </div>
